description._content: Catalog #: 15_001407 Title: Harlow PJC-2 Date: June, 1992 ADDITIONAL INFORMATION: Harlow PJC-2. Designed by Max Harlow in the mid 1930s. The first stressed skin aircraft produced in the U.S. It was named after the Pasadena Junior College (PJC) where its designer, Max Harlow, was an instructor of Aeronautical Engineering. Of eleven produced, 6 are still in existence, 3 of those still flyable. Collection: Charles M. Daniels Collection Photo Album Name: U.S Manufacturers IV, G to L Page #: 9 Tags: Harlow PJC-2 PUBLIC COMMONS.SOURCE INSTITUTION: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
